TITLE: Space race 2.0: Russia, India, China and the U.S. are heading for the lunar south pole
SUMMARY: Uncrewed Russian and Indian spacecraft could land in the area next week, while the U.S. is trying to land astronauts there by 2025

TITLE: Chinese property giant Evergrande files for bankruptcy protection in U.S. court
SUMMARY: The filing by the heavily indebted developer comes amid fears that troubles in the property sector could spill over to other parts of the world’s second-largest economy

TITLE: Pilot dies after mid-flight medical emergency, officials say
SUMMARY: The flight, from Miami to Chile, was diverted to Panama, where the Latam Airlines pilot died after medical treatment, the airline said

TITLE: Private jet crashes onto a highway in Malaysia, killing 8 on board and 2 on the ground
SUMMARY: The small airplane was carrying six passengers and two flight crew when it lost control and crashed into a car and a motorcycle near Kuala Lumpur, the capital of Malaysia, officials said

TITLE: Residents of Canada's Northwest Territories race to flee capital as wildfire nears
SUMMARY: Thousands raced to beat a noon Friday deadline to evacuate their homes as the worst fire season on record in Canada showed no signs of easing

TITLE: Out-of-control wildfire scorches Spain's Tenerife island, affecting thousands
SUMMARY: Spanish authorities said their main goal is to contain the fire and prevent it from reaching more populated areas. on the popular tourist island

TITLE: China's Xi calls for measures to mitigate disastrous flooding amid economic slowdown
SUMMARY: Much of China is having a particularly damp summer, with 142 people killed by flooding in July and dozens more this month

TITLE: North Koreans face increasing repression and threat of starvation, U.N. says
SUMMARY: “People are becoming increasingly desperate,” the U.N. rights chief told the Security Council in its first open meeting on human rights in North Korea since 2017

TITLE: Drone attack on Moscow damages building and disrupts air traffic
SUMMARY: Drone air strikes deep inside Russia have increased since a drone was destroyed over the Kremlin in early May

TITLE: Woman captured in alleged plot to assassinate Ukraine’s Zelenskyy
SUMMARY: Ukraine intelligence says a Russian informant was captured while trying to carry out a plot to assassinate President Zelenskyy during a trip to Mykolaiv last month. Meanwhile, a patrol of 11 Chinese and Russian warships cruised together near Alaska. NBC News’ Richard Engel has more details
